Maintainer: Joshua <joshua@example.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2

Package: immutable-ubuntu
Architecture: all
Depends: btrfs-progs, dracut, systemd-container, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: git, btrbk
Conflicts: initramfs-tools
Description: Immutable Ubuntu root via btrfs snapshots
 Makes an Ubuntu installation effectively immutable by booting from
 read-only btrfs snapshots. A dracut initramfs module creates a writable
 clone at boot, and a staging pipeline handles updates via systemd-nspawn.
 .
 Includes:
  - dracut module for boot-time snapshot cloning
  - GRUB hook for snapshot-based boot entries
  - immutable-update script for staged apt updates and custom scripts
  - immutable-ubuntu-setup for autoinstall bootstrapping
